{% doc %}
  Shoppable Video Stories — Curated. Instagram-style stories layout that
  renders the merchant's hand-picked list of spectrum_shoppable_video
  metaobjects. No source/slot — works on any page (home, custom landing,
  article, etc.). Sibling of qsh181xu (PDP) and n3rzwxe1 (PLP); shares
  runtime + analytics + mini-PDP.

  Wrapper contract (per docs/tech/studio-liquid-snippets.md "Library Snippets"):
    - variant            : default variant from mo.variants.value.variants
    - mo                 : spectrum_snippet_instance metaobject drop
    - mutation_handle    : 'mut-{instanceId}' (consumed by wrapper outer div)
    - experience_handle  : (consumed by wrapper outer div)

  variant.content fields:
    - videos                {array}             list of spectrum_shoppable_video metaobject drops (the merchant's pick)
    - section_title         {string}            heading above the preview tray
    - section_description   {string}            supporting copy
    - preview_shape         {string}            'circle' | 'square' | 'rounded'
    - auto_advance_seconds  {number}            seconds per slide before advance (1–30)
    - mute_on_launch          {boolean}           whether to start muted
    - show_progress_bar       {boolean}           per-slide progress indicator
    - stories_close_on_last   {boolean}           close lightbox after last story; if false the last loops
    - show_preview_play_button {boolean}          overlay a centered play icon on each preview thumbnail
    - cta_text                {string}            label on the per-slide CTA button
    - cta_action              {string}            'redirect' | 'mini_pdp'

  Render strategy:
    - SSR emits the section header + a horizontal preview tray with one button
      per video handle (skeleton placeholder + poster image + label) and the
      fullscreen <dialog> scaffold (close, mute, progress strip, slide track).
    - JS reads the sibling <script type="application/json"
      data-spectrum-snippet-pool> for resolved per-video data (URL, poster,
      product_tags) and replaces previews + builds slides at bind time.
    - Pool keying is by metaobject handle (derived from content.videos).
    - Renders nothing when content.videos is empty.

  @example
  {% render '_sai-snippet-kvb3hsy7',
    variant: variant,
    mo: mo,
    mutation_handle: 'mut-q8x3m2pkabcd1234',
    experience_handle: 'home-experience'
  %}
{% enddoc %}

{% comment %}
  Institutional knowledge:
  - Per-video data resolution lives in the pool block at the bottom of this
    file, not at the preview-render site. JS is the single owner of the
    rendered DOM after bind, mirroring the svmk8tqx pattern.
  - `auto_advance_seconds` defaults via | default: (number; safe to use the
    filter — only `false` and `nil` get replaced, and 0 is not a valid value
    here per `min: 1`).
  - Boolean props (`mute_on_launch`, `show_progress_bar`,
    `stories_close_on_last`, `show_preview_play_button`) use the explicit
    nil-check pattern; Liquid's `| default:` would replace `false` with
    the default.
  - The pool block is a sibling of the <sai-kvb3hsy7> custom element, NOT
    a child — JS reads it via direct-children iteration on the outer
    instance container.
{% endcomment %}

{% stylesheet %}
/* Shoppable Video Stories — Curated (kvb3hsy7) */

/* ==========================================================================
   Shoppable Video Stories — base layout
   --------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Author-static CSS. Per-instance values (background, typography, spacing,
   shadows) come from variant.content.style and bake into a sibling
   <style data-spectrum-style> element. Selectors stay at single-class
   specificity so the per-instance rules win the cascade.
   ========================================================================== */

.sai-kvb3hsy7 {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__container {
  max-width: var(--page-width, 1200px);
  margin-inline: auto;
  padding-inline: 1.5rem;
  padding-block: 1.5rem;
}

/* ── Header ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

.sai-kvb3hsy7__header {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 0.5rem;
  margin-block-end: 1rem;
  align-items: center;
  text-align: center;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__title {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-heading-family, inherit);
  font-weight: var(--font-heading-weight, 600);
  font-size: 1.25rem;
  line-height: 1.25;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__description {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  line-height: 1.4;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  opacity: 0.7;
}

/* ── Preview tray ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

.sai-kvb3hsy7__tray {
  display: flex;
  gap: 0.75rem;
  overflow-x: auto;
  overflow-y: hidden;
  scroll-behavior: smooth;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  padding-block-end: 0.5rem;
  /* Center horizontally when content fits; with `safe`, alignment falls back
     to flex-start when content overflows so the first preview is never
     clipped at the leading edge. */
  justify-content: safe center;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__tray::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}
.sai-kvb3hsy7__tray {
  scrollbar-width: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview {
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 0.375rem;
  padding: 0;
  background: transparent;
  border: none;
  cursor: pointer;
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}

/* Suppress the UA focus ring on pointer/touch + when focus returns
   programmatically after the lightbox closes — only show a visible ring for
   keyboard navigation. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview:focus {
  outline: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
  border-radius: 4px;
}

/* Frame is the outer ring — Instagram-style pink/orange/yellow gradient
   with a 3px white inset between ring and poster. The two-layer
   `padding-box` + `border-box` background trick: padding-box receives
   the white inset, the transparent border sees the gradient through
   border-box. The poster image (set by JS on the inner __preview-poster)
   sits inside the white inset. Same ring on all 3 preview_shape values
   — only the corner radius changes per shape. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame {
  display: block;
  position: relative;
  width: 5.5rem;
  height: 5.5rem;
  padding: 3px;
  border: 3px solid transparent;
  background: linear-gradient(#fff, #fff) padding-box,
    linear-gradient(45deg, #f09433 0%, #e6683c 25%, #dc2743 50%, #cc2366 75%, #bc1888 100%)
    border-box;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
}

/* Per-shape — apply matching radius to BOTH outer frame and inner poster. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-circle .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame,
.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-circle .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
  border-radius: 50%;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-square .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame,
.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-square .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
  border-radius: 0;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-rounded .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame {
  border-radius: 14px;
}
.sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-rounded .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
  /* Inner radius is slightly smaller than outer for a clean concentric look. */
  border-radius: 8px;
}

/* Optional centered play badge — gated by the show_preview_play_button prop.
   Sits above the poster so it appears on every preview shape. The triangle
   icon is built with `currentColor` so the disc + glyph share the same
   white/dark contrast pair. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-play {
  position: absolute;
  top: 50%;
  left: 50%;
  transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
  width: 28px;
  height: 28px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.55);
  color: #fff;
  border-radius: 50%;
  pointer-events: none;
  z-index: 1;
}

/* Author `display: inline-flex` above wins over the UA stylesheet's
   `[hidden] { display: none }` rule, so the toggle requires an explicit
   override at the same specificity. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-play[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-play svg {
  /* Optical centering — the triangle's center of mass sits left of the
     bounding-box center; nudge a hair right so it reads centered in the disc. */
  margin-left: 2px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-label {
  display: block;
  max-width: 5.5rem;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 0.75rem;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  text-align: center;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
}

/* Skeleton state — shimmer on the inner poster while JS upgrades the card.
   Targets __preview-poster (not __preview-frame) so the gradient ring on
   the frame stays untouched while the poster animates. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__preview--placeholder .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
  background-image: linear-gradient(
    90deg,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04) 0%,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08) 50%,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.04) 100%
  );
  background-size: 200% 100%;
  animation: sai-kvb3hsy7-shimmer 1.4s ease-in-out infinite;
}

@keyframes sai-kvb3hsy7-shimmer {
  0% {
    background-position: 200% 0;
  }
  100% {
    background-position: -200% 0;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview--placeholder .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster {
    animation: none;
  }
}

/* ── Fullscreen dialog ──────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog[open] {
  position: fixed;
  inset: 0;
  width: 100vw;
  height: 100dvh;
  max-width: 100vw;
  max-height: 100dvh;
  margin: 0;
  padding: 0;
  background: #000;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  overflow: hidden;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog::backdrop {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.95);
}

/* Close, mute, nav buttons — explicit width/height keeps the circles
   identical regardless of inner icon dimensions. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-close,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav {
  position: absolute;
  width: 36px;
  height: 36px;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);
  border: none;
  color: #fff;
  cursor: pointer;
  z-index: 3;
  border-radius: 50%;
  padding: 0;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

/* Stacked vertically on the right edge — close on top, mute below.
   Same button sizing as before (14/20 px icons, 0.625rem padding). */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-close {
  top: 1rem;
  right: 1rem;
}
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute {
  /* close at top: 1rem (16px) + 36px height = 52px bottom; +36px gap = 88px (5.5rem) */
  top: 5.5rem;
  right: 1rem;
}

/* Defensive — SVG icons inside the mute toggle ignore the [hidden] attribute
   in some user agents (display defaults compete with [hidden]). Force the
   inactive state to display:none. JS toggles `.hidden` between the two SVGs. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute svg[hidden],
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute svg.sai-kvb3hsy7__mute-icon--muted[hidden],
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute svg.sai-kvb3hsy7__mute-icon--sound[hidden] {
  display: none !important;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-close:focus-visible,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute:focus-visible,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #fff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav {
  top: 50%;
  transform: translateY(-50%);
  display: none;
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav:not([hidden]) {
    display: inline-flex;
  }
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav--prev {
  left: 1rem;
}
.sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav--next {
  right: 1rem;
}

/* Progress strip — one segment per slide. On mobile it spans the
   full-bleed slide-frame; on tablet+ it's constrained to match the 9:16
   frame width so it visually belongs to the video, not the dialog. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__progress {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0.75rem;
  left: 1rem;
  right: 1rem;
  display: flex;
  gap: 4px;
  z-index: 4;
}

/* Author `display: flex` above wins over the UA stylesheet's
   `[hidden] { display: none }` rule, so the toggle requires an explicit
   override at the same specificity. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__progress[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__progress {
    left: 50%;
    right: auto;
    transform: translateX(-50%);
    width: min(calc(100% - 2rem), calc(100dvh * 9 / 16 - 2rem));
  }
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__progress-segment {
  flex: 1;
  height: 2px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.3);
  overflow: hidden;
  border-radius: 1px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__progress-fill {
  display: block;
  height: 100%;
  width: 0%;
  background: #fff;
  transition: width 100ms linear;
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__progress-fill {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* Slide track */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__slides {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__slide {
  flex: 0 0 100%;
  height: 100%;
  position: relative;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: #000;
  overflow: hidden;
}

/* On mobile, the frame is full-bleed (fills viewport edge-to-edge). On
   tablet+ it's constrained to 9:16 and centered with a dark backdrop on
   either side — matches the grid lightbox pattern on larger screens. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__slide-frame {
  position: relative;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  background: #000;
  overflow: hidden;
}

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__slide-frame {
    width: auto;
    height: 100%;
    aspect-ratio: 9 / 16;
    max-width: 100%;
  }
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__slide-video {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
  background: #000;
}

/* Asset slots — every slide carries one wrapper per asset (video or image).
   Only one is visible at a time; the rest sit positioned but `hidden`. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__asset {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: #000;
}

/* Author `display: flex` above wins over the UA stylesheet's
   `[hidden] { display: none }` rule, so the toggle requires an explicit
   override at the same specificity. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__asset[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__asset-img {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: contain;
  display: block;
  background: #000;
}

/* ── Product card overlay (matches grid lightbox layout) ───────────────
   Sits inside the 9:16 frame, anchored to the bottom with a gradient mask
   for legibility. 3-column grid: image | title+price | ATC button. */

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-overlay {
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  z-index: 3;
  padding: 12px 12px 16px;
  background: linear-gradient(
    to top,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.72) 0%,
    rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.4) 60%,
    transparent 100%
  );
  pointer-events: auto;
}

/* Horizontal strip — one card per tagged product. Grid sibling pattern:
   flex row + scroll-snap so swipes settle one card at a time on mobile,
   trackpad / drag scrolls feel native on desktop. Scrollbar hidden. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-overlay-scroll {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: row;
  gap: 10px;
  overflow-x: auto;
  overflow-y: hidden;
  scroll-snap-type: x mandatory;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  scrollbar-width: none;
  padding-bottom: 4px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-overlay-scroll::-webkit-scrollbar {
  display: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-card {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 60px 1fr auto;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 10px;
  padding: 8px 10px;
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  color: #1a1a1a;
  border-radius: 12px;
  text-decoration: none;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  /* Default (2+ cards): card takes 80% of the strip — leaves a 20% peek
     of the next card so the user knows there's more to swipe to. The
     :only-child rule below takes over for single-card slides. Width
     scales with the strip on every viewport (no cap). */
  flex: 0 0 80%;
  scroll-snap-align: start;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-overlay-scroll > .sai-kvb3hsy7__product-card:only-child {
  flex: 0 0 100%;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-image-wrap {
  display: block;
  width: 60px;
  height: 60px;
  flex-shrink: 0;
  border-radius: 8px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-image {
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
  display: block;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-meta {
  min-width: 0;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 2px;
  text-align: left;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-title {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  line-height: 1.3;
  color: #1a1a1a;
  white-space: nowrap;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-overflow: ellipsis;
  text-decoration: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__product-price {
  margin: 0;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 600;
  line-height: 1.2;
  color: #1a1a1a;
  opacity: 0.8;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__cta {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  padding: 8px 14px;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 700;
  background: #121212;
  color: #fff;
  border: none;
  border-radius: 6px;
  cursor: pointer;
  text-decoration: none;
  white-space: nowrap;
  line-height: 1;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__cta:hover:not(:disabled) {
  opacity: 0.9;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__cta:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid #fff;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__cta:disabled {
  opacity: 0.4;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

/* ── Mini-PDP bottom sheet (quickshop) ─────────────────────────────────
   Layout adapted from the Lotto theme's `sv-quickshop` pattern: backdrop
   covers the dialog, panel slides up from the bottom on mobile and is
   centered/constrained on tablet+. Theme color + font variables only.
   ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────── */

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  z-index: 12;
  display: flex;
  align-items: flex-end;
  justify-content: center;
  pointer-events: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop[hidden] {
  display: none;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-backdrop {
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
  transition: background 0.25s ease;
  pointer-events: auto;
  cursor: pointer;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop--open .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-backdrop {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.45);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-panel {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 1;
  width: 100%;
  max-height: 88%;
  background: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border-radius: 16px 16px 0 0;
  padding: 20px 20px 22px;
  box-sizing: border-box;
  transform: translateY(100%);
  transition: transform 0.28s cubic-bezier(0.32, 0.72, 0, 1);
  pointer-events: auto;
  overflow-y: auto;
  -webkit-overflow-scrolling: touch;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 18px;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop--open .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-panel {
  transform: translateY(0);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-close {
  position: absolute;
  top: 12px;
  right: 12px;
  width: 32px;
  height: 32px;
  padding: 0;
  background: transparent;
  border: none;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  cursor: pointer;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-close:hover {
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-close:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-header {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 130px 1fr;
  gap: 16px;
  align-items: flex-start;
  padding-right: 36px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-media {
  width: 130px;
  aspect-ratio: 1 / 1;
  border-radius: 8px;
  overflow: hidden;
  background: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.06);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-image {
  display: block;
  width: 100%;
  height: 100%;
  object-fit: cover;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-meta {
  min-width: 0;
  padding-top: 4px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-title {
  display: block;
  font-family: var(--font-heading-family, var(--font-body-family, inherit));
  font-size: 17px;
  line-height: 1.25;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  text-decoration: none;
  margin: 0 0 8px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-title:hover {
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-price {
  margin: 0;
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 6px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-price-compare {
  font-weight: 400;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  opacity: 0.55;
  font-size: 13px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view {
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 4px;
  margin-top: 6px;
  font-size: 12px;
  font-weight: 500;
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  opacity: 0.55;
  text-decoration: none;
  transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view:hover,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view:focus-visible {
  opacity: 0.85;
  text-decoration: underline;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view-icon {
  flex-shrink: 0;
  display: inline-block;
}

/* Options container — N stacked group cards. The card pattern keeps each
   attribute visually scoped + makes the selected-value label legible at a
   glance. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-options {
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 12px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-group {
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.12);
  border-radius: 10px;
  padding: 12px 14px;
  display: flex;
  flex-direction: column;
  gap: 10px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-group-head {
  display: flex;
  align-items: baseline;
  gap: 6px;
  font-size: 13px;
  line-height: 1.2;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-group-name {
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  opacity: 0.55;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-group-selected {
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  font-weight: 600;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-group-pills {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 8px;
}

/* Pill — three flavors. Text-only is the default; swatch-color and
   swatch-image add a leading visual marker but share the same chrome. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill {
  flex: 0 0 auto;
  display: inline-flex;
  align-items: center;
  gap: 8px;
  min-width: 64px;
  padding: 10px 14px;
  background: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.22);
  border-radius: 999px;
  font-family: var(--font-body-family, inherit);
  font-size: 13px;
  font-weight: 600;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: background 0.15s ease, color 0.15s ease, border-color 0.15s ease;
  line-height: 1.2;
  text-align: center;
  box-sizing: border-box;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill:hover {
  border-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.6);
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill--selected,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill--selected:hover {
  border-color: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  border-width: 2px;
  /* Compensate for the +1px border so the pill doesn't shift on select. */
  padding: 9px 13px;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill--oos {
  opacity: 0.45;
  text-decoration: line-through;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

/* Swatch leading element — sits before the label. Color swatches use the
   inline `background-color` set by JS; image swatches use `background-image`.
   Border keeps light swatches legible against a white pill background. */
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill-swatch {
  display: inline-block;
  width: 18px;
  height: 18px;
  border-radius: 50%;
  background-size: cover;
  background-position: center;
  border: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill--swatch-color .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill-swatch,
.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill--swatch-image .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill-swatch {
  /* Selected variants get a thicker outer ring around the swatch to mirror
     the pill's selected state at the swatch level too. */
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-pill-label {
  display: inline-block;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-atc {
  width: 100%;
  margin-top: 4px;
  padding: 18px 20px;
  background: rgb(var(--color-foreground, 18 18 18));
  color: rgb(var(--color-background, 255 255 255));
  border: none;
  border-radius: 4px;
  font-family: var(--font-heading-family, var(--font-body-family, inherit));
  font-size: 15px;
  font-weight: 700;
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 0.06em;
  cursor: pointer;
  transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-atc:hover:not(:disabled) {
  opacity: 0.88;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-atc:disabled {
  opacity: 0.4;
  cursor: not-allowed;
}

.sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-atc:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid currentColor;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}

@media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
  /* Mirror the 9:16 slide-frame width so the bottom sheet visually belongs
     to the video, not the dialog. Same math used by the progress strip. */
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-panel {
    max-width: min(100%, calc(100dvh * 9 / 16));
    border-radius: 16px;
    margin-bottom: 16px;
  }
}

@media (prefers-reduced-motion: reduce) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-panel,
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-backdrop {
    transition: none;
  }
}

/* ── Tablet+ layout tweaks ────────────────────────────────────────────── */

@media (min-width: 750px) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame {
    width: 6.5rem;
    height: 6.5rem;
  }
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__title {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
  }
}

@media (min-width: 990px) {
  .sai-kvb3hsy7__container {
    padding-inline: 2rem;
    padding-block: 2rem;
  }
}
{% endstylesheet %}

<script src="{{ 'sai-snippet-kvb3hsy7.js' | asset_url }}" async></script>

{%- liquid
  assign content = variant.content
  assign section_title = content.section_title | default: 'Stories'
  assign section_description = content.section_description
  assign preview_shape = content.preview_shape | default: 'circle'
  assign auto_advance_seconds = content.auto_advance_seconds | default: 5
  assign cta_text = content.cta_text | default: 'Shop now'
  assign cta_action = content.cta_action | default: 'redirect'
  comment
    Resolve the merchant's curated picks into a string[] of metaobject
    handles. The variant content for a metaobject-list prop is a typed
    reference marker — { kind, refIds: string[] } — so we read .refIds
    directly. That gives us the same shape the PDP/PLP siblings get from
    their slot payload, and the pool block + JS contract are identical
    downstream.
  endcomment
  assign video_handles = content.videos.refIds

  if content.mute_on_launch == nil
    assign mute_on_launch = true
  else
    assign mute_on_launch = content.mute_on_launch
  endif

  if content.show_progress_bar == nil
    assign show_progress_bar = true
  else
    assign show_progress_bar = content.show_progress_bar
  endif

  if content.stories_close_on_last == nil
    assign stories_close_on_last = true
  else
    assign stories_close_on_last = content.stories_close_on_last
  endif

  if content.show_preview_play_button == nil
    assign show_preview_play_button = false
  else
    assign show_preview_play_button = content.show_preview_play_button
  endif

  comment
    Filter video_handles to videos whose product_tags list contains at
    least one tagged product whose referenced Product resolves on the
    storefront. Storefront Liquid returns nil for draft / archived /
    deleted products, so this naturally hides videos whose tagged
    products are all unpublished. If zero videos remain, the outer
    `if video_handles.size > 0` guard below suppresses the entire
    output — tray, dialog, pool — no DOM, no JS bind, no CLS reserved.
  endcomment
  assign _renderable_handles_csv = ''
  for handle in video_handles
    assign _vid = metaobjects.spectrum_shoppable_video[handle]
    assign _has_renderable_tag = false
    if _vid != blank and _vid.product_tags != blank
      for _t in _vid.product_tags.value
        if _t.product.value != blank
          assign _has_renderable_tag = true
          break
        endif
      endfor
    endif
    if _has_renderable_tag
      if _renderable_handles_csv == ''
        assign _renderable_handles_csv = handle
      else
        assign _renderable_handles_csv = _renderable_handles_csv | append: ',' | append: handle
      endif
    endif
  endfor
  if _renderable_handles_csv == ''
    assign video_handles = '' | split: ','
  else
    assign video_handles = _renderable_handles_csv | split: ','
  endif
-%}

{%- if video_handles.size > 0 -%}
<sai-kvb3hsy7
  class="sai-kvb3hsy7 sai-kvb3hsy7--shape-{{ preview_shape }}"
  data-auto-advance-seconds="{{ auto_advance_seconds }}"
  data-mute-on-launch="{{ mute_on_launch }}"
  data-show-progress-bar="{{ show_progress_bar }}"
  data-close-on-last="{{ stories_close_on_last }}"
  data-cta-text="{{ cta_text | escape }}"
  data-cta-action="{{ cta_action }}"
>
  <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__container">
    {%- comment -%}
      Header wrapper + title + description always rendered so applyVariant()
      can flip text without DOM injection when a variant changes either field
      between blank and non-blank. `hidden` attribute drives visibility.
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__header"{% if section_title == blank and section_description == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>
      <h2 class="sai-kvb3hsy7__title"{% if section_title == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>{{ section_title }}</h2>
      <p class="sai-kvb3hsy7__description"{% if section_description == blank %} hidden{% endif %}>{{ section_description }}</p>
    </div>

    {%- comment -%}
      Preview tray — one skeleton button per video handle. JS reads
      data-handle, looks up pool[handle], then upgrades the placeholder
      with the resolved poster + label, or removes it if the video is
      missing from the pool (defensive — visible-degraded over silent skip).
    {%- endcomment -%}
    <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__tray" role="list">
      {%- for handle in video_handles -%}
        <button
          class="sai-kvb3hsy7__preview sai-kvb3hsy7__preview--placeholder"
          type="button"
          role="listitem"
          data-handle="{{ handle }}"
          aria-label="Open story"
        >
          <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-frame">
            <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-poster"></span>
            {%- comment -%}
              Always rendered so applyVariant() can toggle `hidden` without
              injecting DOM when a variant flips show_preview_play_button.
            {%- endcomment -%}
            <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-play" aria-hidden="true"{% unless show_preview_play_button %} hidden{% endunless %}>
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" focusable="false">
                <path d="M3.5 2L11 7L3.5 12V2Z" fill="currentColor" />
              </svg>
            </span>
          </span>
          <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__preview-label" hidden></span>
        </button>
      {%- endfor -%}
    </div>

    <dialog
      class="sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog"
      aria-modal="true"
      aria-label="{{ section_title | default: 'Stories' | escape }}"
    >
      {%- comment -%}
        Always rendered so applyVariant() can toggle `hidden` without
        injecting DOM when a variant flips show_progress_bar.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__progress" aria-hidden="true"{% unless show_progress_bar %} hidden{% endunless %}></div>

      <button
        class="sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-close"
        type="button"
        data-action="close"
        aria-label="Close stories"
      >
        <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
          <path d="M1.5 1.5L12.5 12.5M12.5 1.5L1.5 12.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" />
        </svg>
      </button>

      <button
        class="sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-mute"
        type="button"
        data-action="mute"
        aria-label="Unmute video"
      >
        <svg class="sai-kvb3hsy7__mute-icon--muted" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M11 5L6 9H2v6h4l5 4V5z" fill="currentColor"/>
          <path d="M23 9l-6 6M17 9l6 6" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        </svg>
        <svg class="sai-kvb3hsy7__mute-icon--sound" width="20" height="20" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" style="display: none">
          <path d="M11 5L6 9H2v6h4l5 4V5z" fill="currentColor"/>
          <path d="M15.54 8.46a5 5 0 0 1 0 7.07M19.07 4.93a10 10 0 0 1 0 14.14" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>

      <button
        class="sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav--prev"
        type="button"
        data-action="prev"
        aria-label="Previous story"
        hidden
      >
        <svg width="10" height="16" viewBox="0 0 10 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M9 1L1 8L9 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>
      <button
        class="sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav sai-kvb3hsy7__dialog-nav--next"
        type="button"
        data-action="next"
        aria-label="Next story"
        hidden
      >
        <svg width="10" height="16" viewBox="0 0 10 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
          <path d="M1 1L9 8L1 15" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/>
        </svg>
      </button>

      <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__slides"></div>

      {%- comment -%}
        Mini-PDP bottom sheet — single instance, populated on demand from
        pool data. Sibling of __slides so swipe/transform on slides doesn't
        affect it. Hidden by default; JS toggles `--open` and `hidden`.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      <aside
        class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop"
        role="dialog"
        aria-modal="true"
        aria-labelledby="sai-kvb3hsy7-qs-title"
        hidden
        aria-hidden="true"
      >
        <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-backdrop" data-action="qs-close"></div>
        <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-panel" role="document">
          <button
            type="button"
            class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-close"
            data-action="qs-close"
            aria-label="Close"
            title="Close"
          >
            <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 14 14" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
              <path d="M1.5 1.5L12.5 12.5M12.5 1.5L1.5 12.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" />
            </svg>
          </button>

          <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-header">
            <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-media">
              <img class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-image" data-qs-image alt="" width="600" height="600" loading="lazy" />
            </div>
            <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-meta">
              <a class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-title" data-qs-title id="sai-kvb3hsy7-qs-title" href="#"></a>
              <p class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-price">
                <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-price-current" data-qs-price></span>
                <span class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-price-compare" data-qs-compare hidden></span>
              </p>
              <a class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view" data-qs-view data-action="product-click" href="#">
                View product
                <svg class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-view-icon" width="12" height="12" viewBox="0 0 12 12" fill="none" aria-hidden="true" focusable="false">
                  <path d="M4 2L8 6L4 10" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
                </svg>
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-options" data-qs-options></div>

          <button
            type="button"
            class="sai-kvb3hsy7__quickshop-atc"
            data-action="qs-atc"
            disabled
          >Add to cart</button>
        </div>
      </aside>
    </dialog>
  </div>
</sai-kvb3hsy7>

{%- comment -%}
  Pool block — sibling of <sai-kvb3hsy7>. Carries every video's resolved
  data: video URL (mp4 picked server-side), poster URL (image_url filter
  applied), and the full product_tags array with prices and image URLs
  pre-resolved. JS reads this directly; no client-side Liquid lookups.
{%- endcomment -%}
<script type="application/json" data-spectrum-snippet-pool>
{
  "shoppable_video_stories":{
    {%- for handle in video_handles -%}
      {%- assign video_entry = metaobjects.spectrum_shoppable_video[handle] -%}
      {%- if video_entry -%}
      {%- unless forloop.first -%},{%- endunless -%}

      {%- comment -%}
        Walk the new entry.assets[] reference list (spectrum_shoppable_video_asset
        metaobjects). The parent-level video_source / poster_image fields are
        gone — every playable media now lives on a child asset. Each asset can
        be a video (asset_type: 'video') or an image (asset_type: 'image').
        We collect a flat assets array for the dialog, and also expose the
        first asset's URLs as top-level video_url / poster_url so the tray
        preview upgrade path (upgradePreview) stays a one-shot read.
      {%- endcomment -%}
      {%- assign first_video_url = '' -%}
      {%- assign first_poster_url = '' -%}
      {%- assign first_asset_done = false -%}
      {%- assign total_assets = 0 -%}
      {%- if video_entry.assets != blank -%}
        {%- assign total_assets = video_entry.assets.value.size -%}
        {%- for i in (0..total_assets) -%}
          {%- if i >= total_assets -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
          {%- assign asset = nil -%}
          {%- for a in video_entry.assets.value offset: i limit: 1 -%}
            {%- assign asset = a -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
          {%- if asset -%}
            {%- assign asset_type_val = asset.asset_type.value | default: 'video' -%}
            {%- assign asset_url = '' -%}
            {%- assign asset_poster_url = '' -%}
            {%- assign media_file = asset.media.value -%}
            {%- if media_file != blank -%}
              {%- if asset_type_val == 'image' -%}
                {%- assign asset_url = media_file | image_url: width: 1200 -%}
              {%- else -%}
                {%- if media_file.sources != blank -%}
                  {%- for source in media_file.sources -%}
                    {%- if source.format == 'mp4' and asset_url == '' -%}
                      {%- assign asset_url = source.url -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- endfor -%}
                  {%- if asset_url == '' -%}
                    {%- assign asset_url = media_file.sources.first.url -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- elsif media_file.url != blank -%}
                  {%- assign asset_url = media_file.url -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- endif -%}
            {%- if asset.poster_image.value != blank -%}
              {%- assign asset_poster_url = asset.poster_image.value | image_url: width: 800 -%}
            {%- endif -%}
            {%- unless first_asset_done -%}
              {%- if asset_type_val == 'image' -%}
                {%- assign first_video_url = '' -%}
                {%- assign first_poster_url = asset_url -%}
              {%- else -%}
                {%- assign first_video_url = asset_url -%}
                {%- assign first_poster_url = asset_poster_url -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- assign first_asset_done = true -%}
            {%- endunless -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endfor -%}
      {%- endif -%}

      {{ handle | json }}:{
        "title":{{ video_entry.title | default: '' | json }},
        "video_url":{{ first_video_url | json }},
        "poster_url":{{ first_poster_url | json }},
        "assets":[
          {%- if video_entry.assets != blank -%}
          {%- assign first_asset_json = true -%}
          {%- for i in (0..total_assets) -%}
            {%- if i >= total_assets -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign a_ref = nil -%}
            {%- for ref in video_entry.assets.value offset: i limit: 1 -%}
              {%- assign a_ref = ref -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
            {%- if a_ref -%}
              {%- assign a_type = a_ref.asset_type.value | default: 'video' -%}
              {%- assign a_url = '' -%}
              {%- assign a_poster = '' -%}
              {%- assign a_media = a_ref.media.value -%}
              {%- if a_media != blank -%}
                {%- if a_type == 'image' -%}
                  {%- assign a_url = a_media | image_url: width: 1200 -%}
                {%- else -%}
                  {%- if a_media.sources != blank -%}
                    {%- for source in a_media.sources -%}
                      {%- if source.format == 'mp4' and a_url == '' -%}
                        {%- assign a_url = source.url -%}
                      {%- endif -%}
                    {%- endfor -%}
                    {%- if a_url == '' -%}
                      {%- assign a_url = a_media.sources.first.url -%}
                    {%- endif -%}
                  {%- elsif a_media.url != blank -%}
                    {%- assign a_url = a_media.url -%}
                  {%- endif -%}
                {%- endif -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if a_ref.poster_image.value != blank -%}
                {%- assign a_poster = a_ref.poster_image.value | image_url: width: 800 -%}
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- unless first_asset_json -%},{%- endunless -%}
              {%- assign first_asset_json = false -%}
              {"type":{{ a_type | json }},"url":{{ a_url | json }},"poster_url":{{ a_poster | json }}}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        ],
        "product_tags":[
          {%- comment -%}
            video_entry.product_tags is a list.metaobject_reference of
            spectrum_tagged_product metaobjects (NOT Product drops). We
            iterate via the for+offset+limit:1 idiom (per
            .claude/rules/shopify.md — bracket access + .first are broken
            on reference lists). For each tagged metaobject we resolve the
            actual Product via tagged.product.value and merge with override
            fields (display_name, price, cta_url, thumbnail).
          {%- endcomment -%}
          {%- if video_entry.product_tags != blank -%}
          {%- assign tags_total = video_entry.product_tags.value.size -%}
          {%- assign first_tag = true -%}
          {%- for ti in (0..tags_total) -%}
            {%- if ti >= tags_total -%}{%- break -%}{%- endif -%}
            {%- assign tagged = nil -%}
            {%- for t in video_entry.product_tags.value offset: ti limit: 1 -%}
              {%- assign tagged = t -%}
            {%- endfor -%}
            {%- if tagged -%}
              {%- assign tagged_product = tagged.product.value -%}
              {%- if tagged_product -%}
                {%- assign target_variant = tagged.pre_selected_variant.value | default: tagged_product.selected_or_first_available_variant -%}
                {%- assign display_name = tagged.display_name_override.value | default: tagged_product.title -%}
                {%- assign thumb_img = tagged.thumbnail_override.value | default: tagged_product.featured_image -%}
                {%- assign thumb_url = '' -%}
                {%- if thumb_img != blank -%}
                  {%- assign thumb_url = thumb_img | image_url: width: 600 -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- assign price_str = tagged.price_override.value | default: '' -%}
                {%- if price_str == '' -%}
                  {%- assign price_str = target_variant.price | money -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- assign show_compare = false -%}
                {%- if target_variant.compare_at_price > target_variant.price -%}
                  {%- assign show_compare = true -%}
                {%- endif -%}
                {%- assign url_str = tagged.cta_url_override.value | default: tagged_product.url -%}
                {%- unless first_tag -%},{%- endunless -%}
                {%- assign first_tag = false -%}
                {
                  "id":{{ tagged_product.id | json }},
                  "handle":{{ tagged_product.handle | json }},
                  "title":{{ display_name | json }},
                  "url":{{ url_str | json }},
                  "available":{{ tagged_product.available | json }},
                  "price":{{ price_str | json }},
                  "compare_at_price":{%- if show_compare -%}{{ target_variant.compare_at_price | money | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
                  "image_url":{{ thumb_url | json }},
                  "first_variant_id":{{ target_variant.id | json }},
                  "tag_id":{{ tagged.system.id | json }},
                  "cta_text_override":{{ tagged.cta_text_override.value | json }},
                  "variants":[
                    {%- assign first_v = true -%}
                    {%- for v in tagged_product.variants -%}
                      {%- unless first_v -%},{%- endunless -%}
                      {%- assign first_v = false -%}
                      {%- assign v_img = '' -%}
                      {%- if v.featured_image != blank -%}{%- assign v_img = v.featured_image | image_url: width: 600 -%}{%- endif -%}
                      {
                        "id":{{ v.id | json }},
                        "title":{{ v.title | json }},
                        "available":{{ v.available | json }},
                        "price":{{ v.price | money | json }},
                        "options":[
                          {%- if v.option1 != blank -%}{{ v.option1 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                          {%- if v.option2 != blank -%},{{ v.option2 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                          {%- if v.option3 != blank -%},{{ v.option3 | json }}{%- endif -%}
                        ],
                        "featured_image":{{ v_img | json }}
                      }
                    {%- endfor -%}
                  ],
                  {%- comment -%}
                    Per-product option groupings. We surface name + position + values
                    with optional swatch hints (color hex or image URL) when the
                    merchant has configured them via Shopify's metaobject-based
                    option values. Falls back to plain text pills otherwise.
                  {%- endcomment -%}
                  "options":[
                    {%- assign first_o = true -%}
                    {%- for opt in tagged_product.options_with_values -%}
                      {%- unless first_o -%},{%- endunless -%}
                      {%- assign first_o = false -%}
                      {
                        "name":{{ opt.name | json }},
                        "position":{{ opt.position | json }},
                        "values":[
                          {%- assign first_ov = true -%}
                          {%- for ov in opt.values -%}
                            {%- unless first_ov -%},{%- endunless -%}
                            {%- assign first_ov = false -%}
                            {%- assign sw_color = '' -%}
                            {%- assign sw_image = '' -%}
                            {%- if ov.swatch != blank -%}
                              {%- if ov.swatch.color != blank -%}{%- assign sw_color = ov.swatch.color -%}{%- endif -%}
                              {%- if ov.swatch.image != blank -%}{%- assign sw_image = ov.swatch.image | image_url: width: 80 -%}{%- endif -%}
                            {%- endif -%}
                            {
                              "name":{{ ov.name | json }},
                              "swatch_color":{%- if sw_color != '' -%}{{ sw_color | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%},
                              "swatch_image":{%- if sw_image != '' -%}{{ sw_image | json }}{%- else -%}null{%- endif -%}
                            }
                          {%- endfor -%}
                        ]
                      }
                    {%- endfor -%}
                  ]
                }
              {%- endif -%}
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
          {%- endif -%}
        ]
      }
      {%- endif -%}
    {%- endfor -%}
  }
}
</script>
{%- endif -%}
